00:38:48,166 --> 00:38:56,333
I understand the ordinance and the timeframe that you're looking for, and the meeting to sit down and talk would be very helpful for everybody.

374
00:38:56,353 --> 00:39:00,876
I mean, I'm not gonna throw some things like March 1st to like Memorial Day.

375
00:39:01,157 --> 00:39:03,238
We definitely need leaf blowers at that point.

376
00:39:03,679 --> 00:39:06,020
And I understand somewhat in that timeframe.

377
00:39:07,241 --> 00:39:10,364
October 1st, no, September 15th at least.

378
00:39:11,265 --> 00:39:14,888
I know somebody on the first Zoom meeting wanted to cut us down to December 1st.

379
00:39:15,768 --> 00:39:21,892
We work right the December 15 that there's no snow on the ground oak leaves don't fall until the middle of December.

380
00:39:22,592 --> 00:39:29,216
So, it's things like that sitting down with some landscapers would really be good for people talk about pollution.

381
00:39:30,537 --> 00:39:35,920
I'm 49 years old I've been using a backpack for over 20 years now, I'm as healthy and as fit as I can be.

382
00:39:36,660 --> 00:39:45,291
So they want to talk about pollution, then they want to move us to batteries and batteries themselves, as Georgia mentioned, they could be worse for the environment coming up.

383
00:39:45,971 --> 00:39:55,243
So, if you're going to do backpack blowers and then it's like they said snow blows and this and the noise, I can definitely understand those two areas, the beginning of the season, the end of the season.

384
00:39:55,703 --> 00:40:01,968
You don't hear a blower from December 15 to March 1, if there's no on the ground you don't hear it till April 1.

385
00:40:02,488 --> 00:40:10,495
If I'm fortunate enough to be out March 1 to start making money I'm lucky I have nine months out of the year to do that, and to support these families that we have.

386
00:40:11,215 --> 00:40:14,418
So, I'd be happy to talk more with the council and.

387
00:40:15,517 --> 00:40:16,158
working more on that.

388
00:40:16,198 --> 00:40:19,320
But you have to be realistic to what we do.

389
00:40:19,800 --> 00:40:21,262
A backpack blower to me costs $500.

390
00:40:21,502 --> 00:40:23,964
I have 10 of them.

391
00:40:24,744 --> 00:40:27,647
So you're going to get rid of all that money that I've spent on that.

392
00:40:27,987 --> 00:40:34,432
My lawnmowers, they cost $14,000 to $20,000 to do what we have to do.

393
00:40:34,852 --> 00:40:38,415
There is no way I would be able to do my business without the equipment we have.

394
00:40:39,376 --> 00:40:42,198
I might as well just work by myself and do a couple lawns here and there.

395
00:40:42,698 --> 00:40:43,399
It's impossible.

396
00:40:46,453 --> 00:40:53,297
If you take a look at Medford and Winchester, that's where a lot of my work is, in the 1940s.

397
00:40:53,717 --> 00:40:55,058
You wanna talk about pollution now.

398
00:40:55,318 --> 00:40:58,520
Look how many trees were in this town and that town.

399
00:40:58,820 --> 00:40:59,861
Go look at old photos.

400
00:41:00,641 --> 00:41:06,885
We are enormously, hundreds of thousands more trees than back in the 40s.

401
00:41:07,485 --> 00:41:14,409
So there's plenty of trees out there for, I understand what you're talking about with the pollution, but we also give back to the community too.

402
00:41:16,420 --> 00:41:29,266
There's certain things that this city does, like I watch a certain tree company, they come in here, no dig safe, they go right up on your sidewalks, they break your sidewalks, they plant trees, no dig safe there.

403
00:41:29,906 --> 00:41:45,132
My guys, we have people come into our office during the season and they have a hearing, I forget which company it is, they come in, they talk about eyesight, hearing, so all of my guys when they're using blowers have to have standard hearing equipment and eye protection.

404
00:41:48,736 --> 00:41:52,282
As you said, this is ongoing, and I'm happy to ongo talking about it.

405
00:41:52,302 --> 00:41:55,607
I have kids, of course, I want the world to be safe.

406
00:41:56,569 --> 00:42:00,235
But if you're going to do that, like George says, eliminate everything.

407
00:42:00,876 --> 00:42:01,237
Cars.

408
00:42:01,998 --> 00:42:02,338
everything.

409
00:42:02,358 --> 00:42:03,859
You cannot have electric cars.

410
00:42:04,559 --> 00:42:06,300
Their batteries are worse.

411
00:42:06,480 --> 00:42:13,483
I mean, so I've just, you start here with leaf blowers and the noise, it's just more conversation should definitely be had on it.

412
00:42:13,603 --> 00:42:13,983
That's all.

413
00:42:14,764 --> 00:42:16,764
I'm not the best speaker, but thank you very much.

414
00:42:17,125 --> 00:42:18,225
Have a good one.

415
00:42:18,245 --> 00:42:22,527
Would anyone from the council, I'm sorry, the chamber like to speak?

416
00:42:32,679 --> 00:42:36,141
Good evening everyone my Carol president of the Chamber of Commerce.

417
00:42:37,742 --> 00:42:40,383
I'm encouraged by the conversation that I heard here tonight.

418
00:42:41,164 --> 00:42:47,847
I think it's imperative that you get together with the landscape is the people that use this equipment.

419
00:42:49,337 --> 00:42:57,303
These people provide a great service to the community, as well as their livelihoods and the families that they support.

420
00:42:58,084 --> 00:43:07,992
And it's incumbent upon, if we're gonna move forward, if the city is gonna move forward with an ordinance like this, that there's a happy medium for everybody.

421
00:43:08,072 --> 00:43:10,935
It's not to come in and just say, okay, you can't do this anymore.

422
00:43:11,535 --> 00:43:14,358
You gotta think of the additional added expense to the,

423
00:43:14,878 --> 00:43:26,148
to the homeowner or the person that uses these services, if these companies have to come in and readjust how they're doing things or they have to put, you know, just change everything the way their way of life is.

424
00:43:26,188 --> 00:43:34,074
You know, that's like taking a leaf blower out of a landscaper's hands, like a ton of dentists who can't use a drill in their teeth.

425
00:43:34,155 --> 00:43:42,362
You know, it's just, it just doesn't make sense unless you have the proper conversation and you get together with the people that, that's their business.

426
00:43:43,354 --> 00:43:55,943
No one wants to hurt the community or pollution or anything, but you can't ask a body that does not involve in the business to make decisions for someone that has a business.

427
00:43:56,563 --> 00:43:58,425
So that's all I'd ask.

428
00:43:58,485 --> 00:43:59,445
Keep inviting us to that.

429
00:43:59,765 --> 00:44:02,567
Let's have conversation and we'll be there with you.

430
00:44:02,587 --> 00:44:03,288
Okay, thank you.

