458
00:45:59,059 --> 00:46:01,921
And I think that we can reach a regulation that

459
00:46:05,528 --> 00:46:08,673
hit somewhere in the middle of what people on one side want and what other people want.

460
00:46:09,373 --> 00:46:17,905
Mr. Kearse mentioned someone came on to a previous meeting and wants basically just no leaf blowers anywhere ever in the city, you know, that's a position that someone has.

461
00:46:19,027 --> 00:46:25,188
And there may be a position of a business that has, we want as much possible freedom as we can have to make the decisions that we want as our business.

462
00:46:25,848 --> 00:46:35,070
And it's our job to find somewhere in the middle where businesses can do their work and where the interests of people who want noise and pollution addressed is addressed.

463
00:46:35,150 --> 00:46:36,951
So I think that's the goal of this process.

464
00:46:38,191 --> 00:46:41,492
And I don't think anyone here was thinking we're gonna finish this tonight.

465
00:46:41,872 --> 00:46:44,312
So at least behind this rail, I don't think anyone thought that.

466
00:46:44,392 --> 00:46:46,733
So that's where we're gonna move forward.

467
00:46:48,510 --> 00:47:00,957
you know, part of the work that we do here is that we may reach a compromise where there's pieces of it that some folks are happy with, and pieces of it that other folks are happy with, and pieces that some folks aren't happy with, and pieces that other folks aren't happy with.

468
00:47:01,057 --> 00:47:05,619
So it's difficult work, and I think we're sitting here ready to do it.

469
00:47:05,759 --> 00:47:06,079
Thank you.

470
00:47:06,860 --> 00:47:07,820
Thank you, Vice President Behrs.

471
00:47:08,300 --> 00:47:16,905
